<div id="content">

<p>Welcome to my website. As you may have guessed from the
text above, I work in the <a href=
"http://www.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk">School of Computer Science</a> at
the <a href="http://www.st-andrews.ac.uk">University of St
Andrews</a> in Scotland. Please browse the links to find out more
about me and what I do, or take a look at my <a href=
"research/pubs.php">papers</a>. Or here are some ways to <a href=
"about/contact.php">contact me</a>.</p>

<hr />

<h3>Notices</h3>

<ul>

<li>My (now-graduated) Senior Honours student, Ali Scott, came second 
in the <a
href="http://www.scotlandis.com/ScotSoft2010/YoungSoftwareEngineeroftheYear">Young 
Software Engineer of the Year</a> awards. <b>UPDATE</b>: photo <a 
href="http://www.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/?q=node/4295">here</a>.</li>

<li>My student <a href="http://www.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/~ip/">Iain</a> won the <a 
href="http://cnd.iit.cnr.it/mobiopp2010/Award%20mobiopp%202010-PhD.pdf">PhD 
award</a> at <a 
href="http://cnd.iit.cnr.it/mobiopp2010/">MobiOpp</a>.</li>

<li>We made it to the finals of the <a 
href="http://www.scottishtechnologyprize.com/">Thales Scottish 
Technology Prize</a>.</li>

<li>St Andrews 600th Anniversary <a 
href="http://timecapsule.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/">Time Capsule</a> 
launched.</li>

<li>Some new <a 
href="http://www.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/~tristan/research/pubs.php">papers</a> 
are coming out of our <a href="http://www.pvnets.org">Privacy
Value Networks</a> research project.</li>

<li>New funded PhD opportunities in <a 
href="http://www.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/stacc">Cloud Computing</a>.</li>

<li>In general I am always on the lookout for good PhD students 
&mdash; see my <a href=
"research/">research page</a> for more. Funding is currently
available for qualified students (including overseas students) &mdash; 
see the <a href=
"http://www.sicsa.ac.uk/graduate-academy/prize-studentships/sicsa-prize-studentships/">
SICSA</a> pages. Note that I do <b>not</b> have funding
for overseas undergraduate internships &mdash; the numerous 
requests that I receive for these are ignored.</li>

<li>We hold regular <a 
href="http://scone.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/">SCONE</a>
(SCOttish Networking Event) meetings for anyone who is interested in 
networking and systems. Our next meeting is at the University of 
Aberdeen on <a 
href="http://scone.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/wiki/Meeting04032011">4 
March</a> - please come!
</li>

<li>I am the School Admissions Officer.
If you are thinking about studying Computer Science at St Andrews, 
take a look at the relevant <a href=
"http://www.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/prospective-ug">School webpages</a>
and please consider <a href=
"http://www.st-andrews.ac.uk/admissions/VisitingtheUniversity/Undergraduatevisits/">visiting
us</a>.</li>

<li>I am currently involved with the following events. Please
consider submitting something if you can.

<ul>
<li>Workshop Organiser, <a href="http://conferences.sigcomm.org/sigcomm/2011/workshops/Education/CFPSIGCOMMEducationWorkshop.pdf">SIGCOMM 2011 Education Workshop</a></li>
<li>Workshop Organiser, <a href="http://di.ncl.ac.uk/bhci-securityprivacy/">Health, Wealth and Identity Theft: Designing and evaluating usable security and privacy mechanisms for online happiness</a></li>
<li>Programme Committee, <a href="http://www.acmmm11.org/">ACM Multimedia 2011</a></li>
<li>Steering Committee, <a href="http://www.discover.uottawa.ca/netgames2011/">NetGames 2011</a></li>
<li>Steering Committee, <a href="http://www.hotplanetconf.net/11/">HotPlanet 2011</a></li>
<li>Programme Committee, <a href="http://www.trust2011.org/">Trust 2011</a></li>
<li>Programme Committee, <a href="http://www.iaria.org/conferences2011/SOTICS11.html">SOTICS 2011</a></li>
<li>Programme Committee, <a href="http://www.stevens.edu/pmmps/">PMMPS '11</a></li>
<li>Programme Committee, <a href="http://www.mmsys.org/">Multimedia Systems 2011</a></li>
</ul>
</li>

</ul>

